    question: "How much does a decanter centrifuge cost?",
    answer: "A new decanter centrifuge from a quality, established manufacturer starts from around $50,000 for a small capacity unit to over $1 million for a large capacity machine. Remanufactured models typically cost 40% to 60% of comparable new models. Additional accessories such as explosion-proof upgrades, control systems, and pumps add to the cost."
