  <p><strong>A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decanter_Centrifuge">decanter centrifuge</a> is an industrial centrifuge that continuously separates solids from liquids. The separation in the decanter occurs due to the high centrifugal force generated by its rotating bowl.</strong></p>

  <p>Solid particles need a higher density than liquid for a decanter centrifuge to work.</p>

  <!-- Hero Image Below Fold -->
  <img src="/images/decanter-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-ALDEC-406-Decanter-Dewatering-Centrifuge-for-Sludge-Thickening-600.webp" alt="Alfa Laval ALDEC-406 Decanter Dewatering Centrifuge for Sludge Thickening" width="600" height="407" loading="lazy" class="rounded-lg w-full mb-2" />
